Lebor GabÃ¡la Ãrenn.0101	The Tuatha DÃ© Danann enjoy one hundred and fifty years of unbroken rule .
Lebor GabÃ¡la Ãrenn.0102	Milesians The story of the Gaels , which was interrupted at the end of Book 2 , is now resumed .
Lebor GabÃ¡la Ãrenn.0103	Ãth , who has spied Ireland from the top of BreogÃ¡n 's Tower , journeys to Ireland to investigate his discovery .
Lebor GabÃ¡la Ãrenn.0104	There he is welcomed by the rulers , but jealous nobles kill him and his men return to Iberia with his body .
Lebor GabÃ¡la Ãrenn.0105	The Milesians , or sons of his uncle MÃ­l EspÃ¡ine , set out to avenge his death and conquer the island .
